<br>
You're right though.  Since the delay seems to get rounded up to the nearest integer delay, the same percentage haste often affects different delay weapons slightly differently.  It's best to take that into account when making a comparison.<br>
<br>
13/20 + no haste = 13/20 = .65<br>
13/20 + 40% haste = 13/15 = .867<br>
13/20 + 100-110% haste = 13/10 = 1.3<br>
<br>
15/22 + no haste = 15/22 = .682 = about 4.9% better than 13/20.<br>
15/22 + 40% haste = 15/16 = .938 = about 8.2% better than 13/15.<br>
15/22 + 100-110% haste = 15/11 = 1.36 = about 4.6% better than 13/10.<br>
<br>
As you can see, there's not really a trend that it follows.  You should always check the hasted delay that you expect to be at, before comparing ratios.  I had a cool excel sheet with graph made of this, but excel crashed before I could save it.  Figures. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugaldraith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galdraith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/19/02 11:49:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10773.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 15/22 or 13/20?</span><hr size=1> I always have difficulty calculating the backstab damage part.  How does an 11/17 stack against Ragebringer in the main hand in terms of DPS?  Including backstabs of course. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uketocon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ketocon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/19/02 12:50:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10773.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 15/22 or 13/20?</span><hr size=1> seems to me that only one person flames <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhegwindownfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hegwin Downfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/19/02 3:31:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10773.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 15/22 or 13/20?</span><hr size=1> It's all in the backstab.<br>
<br>
Calculate out your max damage over the course of a 60 second fight with the following assumptions:<br>
<br>
1.  single attack, primary hand only, do not count dual wield/double attack rolls.<br>
2.  Haste to be consistant with any weapons used.  Factor it out of the equation. <br>
3.  Assume that you will hit for max damage each time you swing.<br>
<br>
Weapons of consideration:<br>
8/17 Locustlore.  Max BS recorded:  161<br>
13/27 Serp Tooth.  Max BS Recorded:  287<br>
<br>
Level Damage Bonus:  5.<br>
<br>
Net Base Weapon Damages:<br>
<br>
Locustlore:  13/17 + Str Bonus (10)<br>
       (13*2) + 10 = 36 damage per hit.<br>
Serp Tooth:  18/27 + Str Bonus (10)<br>
       (18*2) +10 = 46 damage per hit.<br>
<br>
Player:  L40 Dwarven Rogue w/ str of 199 <br>
<br>
*****CAVEAT:  Yes, in the case of ANY other melee class, I already agree, LL is a better weapon for MELEE damages.  Please see results - rogues are NOT ordinary MELEE.<br>
<br>
<br>
Example:  60 seconds of straight fighting.<br>
<br>
Locust Lore damage:  17 delay = one swing per 1.7 seconds.<br>
result:  35.29 swings per minute x max damage per round (36) = 1,270.59 damage per round without BS.<br>
<br>
Serp Tooth Damage:  27 delay = one swing per 2.7 seconds.<br>
result:  22.22 swings per minite x max damage per round (46)<br>
= 1,022.12 damage per round without BS.<br>
<br>
<br>
NOW we see the great equalizer:  the Backstab.  Backstab refresh is fixed at 10 seconds.  6 Backstabs per 60 seconds.  Backstab refresh is completely unaffected by weapon delay (test it with a stopwatch if you don't believe me)<br>
<br>
Assume full damage per BS, with a hit each time.<br>
<br>
LocustLore max BS = 161 x 6 = 966 damage in 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
Serp Tooth max BS = 287 x 6 = 1,722 damage in 60 seconds.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
END RESULT OF 60 SECOND FIGHT.<br>
LocustLore total damage:  1,270.59 + 966 = 2,236<br>
Serp Tooth total damage:  1,022.12 + 1,722 = 2,744.12.<br>
<br>
<br>
IF backstab refresh were linked to weapon delay, I would completely agree with you that the faster weap is better.  It's not.  <br>
